info.description: This is the public Twilio REST API.
info.title: Twilio REST API

get.description: Retrieve a list of all Fleets belonging to your account.

post.description: Create a new Fleet for scoping of deployed devices within your account.

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Fleet, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

get.description: Retrieve a list of all Certificate credentials belonging to the Fleet.

parameters.description: Filters the resulting list of Certificates by a unique string identifier of an authenticated Device.
parameters.name: DeviceSid

post.description: Enroll a new Certificate credential to the Fleet, optionally giving it a friendly name and assigning to a Device.

parameters.description: Provides a URL encoded representation of the public certificate in PEM format.
parameters.name: CertificateData

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Certificate credential, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides the unique string identifier of an existing Device to become authenticated with this Certificate credential.
parameters.name: DeviceSid

delete.description: Unregister a specific Certificate credential from the Fleet, effectively disallowing any inbound client connections that are presenting it.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Certificate credential resource.
parameters.name: Sid

get.description: Fetch information about a specific Certificate credential in the Fleet.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Certificate credential resource.
parameters.name: Sid

post.description: Update the given properties of a specific Certificate credential in the Fleet, giving it a friendly name or assigning to a Device.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Certificate credential resource.
parameters.name: Sid

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Certificate credential, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides the unique string identifier of an existing Device to become authenticated with this Certificate credential.
parameters.name: DeviceSid

get.description: Retrieve a list of all Deployments belonging to the Fleet.

post.description: Create a new Deployment in the Fleet, optionally giving it a friendly name and linking to a specific Twilio Sync service instance.

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Deployment, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides the unique string identifier of the Twilio Sync service instance that will be linked to and accessible by this Deployment.
parameters.name: SyncServiceSid

delete.description: Delete a specific Deployment from the Fleet, leaving associated devices effectively undeployed.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Deployment resource.
parameters.name: Sid

get.description: Fetch information about a specific Deployment in the Fleet.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Deployment resource.
parameters.name: Sid

post.description: Update the given properties of a specific Deployment credential in the Fleet, giving it a friendly name or linking to a specific Twilio Sync service instance.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Deployment resource.
parameters.name: Sid

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Deployment, up to 64 characters long
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides the unique string identifier of the Twilio Sync service instance that will be linked to and accessible by this Deployment.
parameters.name: SyncServiceSid

get.description: Retrieve a list of all Devices belonging to the Fleet.

parameters.description: Filters the resulting list of Devices by a unique string identifier of the Deployment they are associated with.
parameters.name: DeploymentSid

post.description: Create a new Device in the Fleet, optionally giving it a unique name, friendly name, and assigning to a Deployment and/or human identity.

parameters.description: Provides a unique and addressable name to be assigned to this Device, to be used in addition to SID, up to 128 characters long.
parameters.name: UniqueName

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text to be assigned to this Device, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides an arbitrary string identifier representing a human user to be associated with this Device, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: Identity

parameters.description: Specifies the unique string identifier of the Deployment group that this Device is going to be associated with.
parameters.name: DeploymentSid

delete.description: Delete a specific Device from the Fleet, also removing it from associated Deployments.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Device resource.
parameters.name: Sid

get.description: Fetch information about a specific Device in the Fleet.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Device resource.
parameters.name: Sid

post.description: Update the given properties of a specific Device in the Fleet, giving it a friendly name, assigning to a Deployment, or a human identity.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Device resource.
parameters.name: Sid

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text to be assigned to this Device, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides an arbitrary string identifier representing a human user to be associated with this Device, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: Identity

parameters.description: Specifies the unique string identifier of the Deployment group that this Device is going to be associated with.
parameters.name: DeploymentSid

get.description: Retrieve a list of all Keys credentials belonging to the Fleet.

parameters.description: Filters the resulting list of Keys by a unique string identifier of an authenticated Device.
parameters.name: DeviceSid

post.description: Create a new Key credential in the Fleet, optionally giving it a friendly name and assigning to a Device.

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Key credential, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides the unique string identifier of an existing Device to become authenticated with this Key credential.
parameters.name: DeviceSid

delete.description: Delete a specific Key credential from the Fleet, effectively disallowing any inbound client connections that are presenting it.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Key credential resource.
parameters.name: Sid

get.description: Fetch information about a specific Key credential in the Fleet.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Key credential resource.
parameters.name: Sid

post.description: Update the given properties of a specific Key credential in the Fleet, giving it a friendly name or assigning to a Device.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Key credential resource.
parameters.name: Sid

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Key credential, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides the unique string identifier of an existing Device to become authenticated with this Key credential.
parameters.name: DeviceSid

delete.description: Delete a specific Fleet from your account, also destroys all nested resources: Devices, Deployments, Certificates, Keys.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Fleet resource.
parameters.name: Sid

get.description: Fetch information about a specific Fleet in your account.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Fleet resource.
parameters.name: Sid

post.description: Update the friendly name property of a specific Fleet in your account.

parameters.description: Provides a 34 character string that uniquely identifies the requested Fleet resource.
parameters.name: Sid

parameters.description: Provides a human readable descriptive text for this Fleet, up to 256 characters long.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides a string identifier of a Deployment that is going to be used as a default one for this Fleet.
parameters.name: DefaultDeploymentSid

See the section entitled [Status Values](https://www.twilio.com/docs/api/phone-numbers/hosted-number-authorization-documents#status-values) for more information on each of these statuses.

parameters.description: An E164 formatted phone number hosted by this HostedNumberOrder.
parameters.name: PhoneNumber

parameters.description: A 34 character string that uniquely identifies the IncomingPhoneNumber resource created by this HostedNumberOrder.
parameters.name: IncomingPhoneNumberSid

parameters.description: A human readable description of this resource, up to 64 characters.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides a unique and addressable name to be assigned to this HostedNumberOrder, assigned by the developer, to be optionally used in addition to SID.
parameters.name: UniqueName

get.description: Retrieve a list of HostedNumberOrders belonging to the account initiating the request.

parameters.description: The Status of this HostedNumberOrder. One of `received`, `pending-verification`, `verified`, `pending-loa`, `carrier-processing`, `testing`, `completed`, `failed`, or `action-required`.
parameters.name: Status

parameters.description: An E164 formatted phone number hosted by this HostedNumberOrder.
parameters.name: PhoneNumber

parameters.description: A 34 character string that uniquely identifies the IncomingPhoneNumber resource created by this HostedNumberOrder.
parameters.name: IncomingPhoneNumberSid

parameters.description: A human readable description of this resource, up to 64 characters.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Provides a unique and addressable name to be assigned to this HostedNumberOrder, assigned by the developer, to be optionally used in addition to SID.
parameters.name: UniqueName

post.description: Host a phone number's capability on Twilio's platform.

parameters.description: The number to host in [+E.164](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E.164) format
parameters.name: PhoneNumber

parameters.description: Used to specify that the SMS capability will be hosted on Twilio's platform.
parameters.name: SmsCapability

parameters.description: This defaults to the AccountSid of the authorization the user is using. This can be provided to specify a subaccount to add the HostedNumberOrder to.
parameters.name: AccountSid

parameters.description: A 64 character string that is a human readable text that describes this resource.
parameters.name: FriendlyName

parameters.description: Optional. Provides a unique and addressable name to be assigned to this HostedNumberOrder, assigned by the developer, to be optionally used in addition to SID.
parameters.name: UniqueName

parameters.description: Optional. A list of emails that the LOA document for this HostedNumberOrder will be carbon copied to.
parameters.name: CcEmails

parameters.description: The URL that Twilio should request when somebody sends an SMS to the phone number. This will be copied onto the IncomingPhoneNumber resource.
parameters.name: SmsUrl

parameters.description: The HTTP method that should be used to request the SmsUrl. Must be either `GET` or `POST`.  This will be copied onto the IncomingPhoneNumber resource.
parameters.name: SmsMethod

parameters.description: A URL that Twilio will request if an error occurs requesting or executing the TwiML defined by SmsUrl. This will be copied onto the IncomingPhoneNumber resource.
parameters.name: SmsFallbackUrl

parameters.description: The HTTP method that should be used to request the SmsFallbackUrl. Must be either `GET` or `POST`. This will be copied onto the IncomingPhoneNumber resource.
parameters.name: SmsFallbackMethod

parameters.description: Optional. The Status Callback URL attached to the IncomingPhoneNumber resource.
parameters.name: StatusCallbackUrl

parameters.description: Optional. The Status Callback Method attached to the IncomingPhoneNumber resource.
parameters.name: StatusCallbackMethod

parameters.description: Optional. The 34 character sid of the application Twilio should use to handle SMS messages sent to this number. If a `SmsApplicationSid` is present, Twilio will ignore all of the SMS urls above and use those set on the application.
parameters.name: SmsApplicationSid

parameters.description: Optional. A 34 character string that uniquely identifies the Address resource that represents the address of the owner of this phone number.
parameters.name: AddressSid

parameters.description: Optional. Email of the owner of this phone number that is being hosted.
parameters.name: Email

parameters.description: Optional. The method used for verifying ownership of the number to be hosted. One of phone-call (default) or phone-bill.
parameters.name: VerificationType

parameters.description: Optional. The unique sid identifier of the Identity Document that represents the document for verifying ownership of the number to be hosted. Required when VerificationType is phone-bill.
parameters.name: VerificationDocumentSid

delete.description: Cancel the HostedNumberOrder (only available when the status is in `received`).

parameters.description: A 34 character string that uniquely identifies this HostedNumberOrder.

parameters.description: User can only post to `pending-verification` status to transition the HostedNumberOrder to initiate a verification call or verification of ownership with a copy of a phone bill.
parameters.name: Status

parameters.description: A verification code that is given to the user via a phone call to the phone number that is being hosted.

parameters.description: Optional. The method used for verifying ownership of the number to be hosted. One of phone-call (default) or phone-bill.
parameters.name: VerificationType

parameters.description: Optional. The unique sid identifier of the Identity Document that represents the document for verifying ownership of the number to be hosted. Required when VerificationType is phone-bill.

parameters.description: Digits to dial after connecting the verification call.

parameters.description: The number of seconds, between 0 and 60, to delay before initiating the verification call. Defaults to 0.
